# Force LF in the working tree for all text files on every platform.
#
# Rationale: rustfmt is configured with `newline_style = "Unix"` (LF), and CI
# runs `cargo fmt --all -- --check` on windows-latest, where git defaults to
# core.autocrlf=true. Without this pin a fresh CI checkout would convert the
# LF-stored blobs to CRLF in the working tree, and the fmt gate would fail even
# though every file is stored as LF. `eol=lf` overrides autocrlf so checkouts
# stay LF and local == CI.
#
# `text=auto` lets git auto-detect text vs binary; detected-binary files are
# left untouched. The vendored wezterm submodule has its own git repo and is
# not governed by this file.
* text=auto eol=lf
